    \label{pygce:analysis:TimelineDataAnalysis:cluster_analyze}
    \index{pygce \textit{(package)}!pygce.analysis \textit{(module)}!pygce.analysis.TimelineDataAnalysis \textit{(class)}!pygce.analysis.TimelineDataAnalysis.cluster\_analyze \textit{(method)}}

    \vspace{0.5ex}

\hspace{.8\funcindent}\begin{boxedminipage}{\funcwidth}

    \raggedright \textbf{cluster\_analyze}(\textit{self})

    \vspace{-1.5ex}

    \rule{\textwidth}{0.5\fboxrule}
\setlength{\parskip}{2ex}
\begin{alltt}

:return: void
    Computes cluster analysis: see days based on differences.
    Each day is different from one another, there are days where you trained more, others where you ate more ...
    The goal is to divide your days into categories (e.g highly-active, active ...) based on data logs.
\end{alltt}

\setlength{\parskip}{1ex}
    \end{boxedminipage}
